    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** - May 11, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🎙️ OpenAI made voice agents harder to ignore\n\nThe chatbot has discovered the phone call, which should comfort absolutely everyone who enjoys being interrupted by software.\n\n- **The launch:** OpenAI released GPT-Realtime-2, GPT-Realtime-Translate and GPT-Realtime-Whisper in the Realtime API on May 7.\n- **The split:** Translate handles live speech translation across more than 70 input languages and 13 output languages, while Whisper does streaming transcription.\n- **The platform move:** Microsoft said the same models are rolling into Azure AI Foundry, turning voice AI into another cloud procurement line item.\n\n*Text boxes were apparently just the training wheels for agents that talk back in real time.*\n\n**Sources:** [OpenAI](https://openai.com/index/advancing-voice-intelligence-with-new-models-in-the-api/) | [Microsoft](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/azure-ai-foundry-blog/a-new-chapter-for-realtime-ai-reasoning-translation-and-real-time-transcription/4517124)\n\n---\n\n## 🧵 Nvidia bought itself a fiber aisle\n\nThe AI factory bottleneck tour has reached optical cable, because even GPUs need plumbing with a press release.\n\n- **The deal:** Nvidia and Corning announced a long-term partnership to expand U.S. optical connectivity capacity 10x for AI infrastructure.\n- **The buildout:** Corning says it will build three new manufacturing plants, create more than 3,000 jobs and supply fiber, cable and connectivity for hyperscale data centers.\n- **The why:** modern AI workloads need thousands of Nvidia GPUs moving data at high speed, making optics a strategic dependency rather than boring cabling.\n\n*The chip war now includes glass. Congratulations to the supply chain, it remains undefeated.*\n\n**Sources:** [Corning](https://www.corning.com/worldwide/en/about-us/news-events/news-releases/2026/05/nvidia-and-corning-announce-long-term-partnership-to-strengthen-us-manufacturing-for-ai-infrastructure.html) | [Tom's Hardware](https://www.tomshardware.com/tech-industry/artificial-intelligence/nvidia-invests-usd300-million-in-corning-to-build-three-new-us-based-optical-fiber-plants-ai-infrastructure-deal-would-boost-fiber-production-capacity-by-over-50-percent)\n\n---\n\n## 🧇 Cerebras priced the wafer-scale IPO circus\n\nNothing says AI infrastructure discipline like asking public markets to bless a chip company at skyscraper valuation speed.\n\n- **The target:** Reuters reports Cerebras is seeking a valuation of up to $26.62 billion in its U.S. IPO.\n- **The raise:** TechCrunch says the offering could raise about $3.5 billion at the high end and become the largest tech IPO of 2026 so far.\n- **The customer gravity:** Cerebras has leaned on OpenAI demand and wafer-scale chips as investors hunt for anything that looks like a Nvidia alternative.\n\n*Public markets wanted AI exposure. Cerebras arrived carrying a prospectus and a very large silicon pancake.*\n\n**Sources:** [Reuters via WSAU](https://wsau.com/2026/05/04/ai-chipmaker-cerebras-targets-115-125-share-price-in-us-ipo-source-says/) | [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/04/openais-cozy-partner-cerebras-is-on-track-for-a-blockbuster-ipo/)\n\n---\n\n## ✂️ ChatGPT got a default model that talks less\n\nOpenAI has identified the product feature users secretly wanted: fewer paragraphs from the machine that generates paragraphs.\n\n- **The rollout:** OpenAI made GPT-5.5 Instant the default model for all ChatGPT users and exposed it in the API as `chat-latest`.\n- **The claim:** OpenAI says it is clearer, more personalized and better at matching answer length to the task.\n- **The metric:** Axios says OpenAI reported 52.5% fewer hallucinated claims than GPT-5.3 Instant on high-stakes medicine, law and finance prompts.\n\n*At last, the AI assistant is being optimized for the ancient technology known as getting to the point.*\n\n**Sources:** [OpenAI](https://openai.com/index/gpt-5-5-instant/) | [Axios](https://www.axios.com/2026/05/05/openai-chatgpt-update-default-model)\n"
  }
]
